property-context-hook.py — wiring & behaviour
==============================================

WHAT IT DOES
A Claude Code `UserPromptSubmit` hook. On every prompt it matches the text against the live
property feed (names + domains + aliases). On a hit it injects that property's VERIFIED current
state (live/up, host, repo-vs-deployed drift, measurement IDs) plus a just-now HTTP probe of the
top match's domain. The harness runs this — not the model — so the truth can't be skipped.

DATA SOURCE (since 2026-07-02)
The CC table `public.property_state` (Supabase, written nightly by the `property-state-cc`
Railway cron at 01:05). The hook GETs the latest row's `payload` via Supabase REST with a hard
3-second timeout, and caches it at /tmp/property-context-hook-feed-cache.json for 5 minutes so
prompts never wait on the network twice. Credentials: `CC_SUPABASE_URL`/`CC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY`
env vars if set, else ~/.config/pete-secrets/command-centre-supabase-keys.json (the one permanent
local key), else the bootstrapped copy under $VAULT/Library/processes/secrets/.

FAIL-OPEN CONTRACT
Any error at any stage (no keys, no network, CC down, bad JSON) → exit 0, inject nothing, never
block or delay the user's prompt beyond the 3s cap. The injected text is key-pattern-sanitised
(SECRET_RE) and capped at 4000 chars.

WIRING (settings.json)
Add under `hooks.UserPromptSubmit` in ~/.claude/settings.json:

  "UserPromptSubmit": [
    {
      "matcher": "",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "[ -f /tmp/pbs/property-context-hook.py ] && python3 /tmp/pbs/property-context-hook.py || true"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]

The `[ -f ... ]` guard means the hook silently no-ops before the session bootstrap has cloned
/tmp/pbs — it never errors on a fresh boot.

VERIFYING IT WORKS
  echo '{"prompt": "how is canary detect doing"}' | python3 /tmp/pbs/property-context-hook.py
should print a JSON hookSpecificOutput block with that property's state. An empty exit-0 means
either no match (try a real property name) or the feed fetch failed (check the key file).

HISTORY
Originally read a local vault file (Library/processes/property-state.json) generated by
property-live-state.py from Properties/*/README.md. Both were retired in the 24 Jun 2026
Business OS thin-client cutover; the hook was unwired from settings.json at the same time.
Rewired onto the CC cloud feed 2026-07-02 (Item 5 of
plan-pete-brain-scripts-local-vault-remediation-2026-07-02).
